text: The twenty-cent coin is part of the Australian decimal currency system. It replaced the florin on the 14th of February, 1966. The florin was for two shillings. As the system changed, the Australian pound became worth two Australian dollars. On the obverse side, there is the Queen Elizabeth of Australia. On the other side, there is a platypus. ==References== * ==Other websites== * Australian Decimal Currency * 20 cent coin collection * The Royal Australian Mint Category:Currency of Australia
